page.title: 14BARNWELL PARK _ WILDLIFE
page.content: Barnwell Park has a main refuge in the middle of a lake.The kingfisher hide which is on flat land is in a tree- hut.You are not allowed to fish there because it is the main kingfishers' hide.There are many nest boxes to encourage birds. The type of birds you can see are geese, coots, mallard, moorhen and swans. You can also see various animals particularly rabbits which are in the warren.When you go to a country park you must not drop any litter. More wildlife could be introduced but not too much because it will get over crowded.
